Q3)Given a number divide it by 2 until you reach 1 -- Ans : log N base 2
5 by2-> 2 by2-> 1 (2 divisions) = log 5 base 2 = 2.12344
9 by2-> 4 by2-> 2 by2-> 1 (3 divisions) = log 9 base 2 = 3.17
15 by2-> 7 by2-> 3 by2-> 1 (3 divisions) = log 15 base 2 = 3.90

......................
2 by2 1 (1 divisions)
4 by2 2 by2 1 (2 divisions)
8 by2 4 by2 2 by2 1 (3 divisions)

so log2 ^ 8 = 3
